			    STPJS 281</div>
  <p class="cont">ence to destroy the children that I was blessing, and I strove with all the faith and spirit<span class="footRef">1</span> that I had
  to seal upon them a blessing<span class="footRef">2</span> that would secure their lives upon the earth; and so much virtue went
  out of me<span class="footRef">3</span> into the children, that I became weak, from which I have not yet recovered; and I referred
  to the case of the woman touching the hem of the garment of Jesus. (Luke, 8th chapter.)<span class="footRef">4</span> The virtue
  here referred to is the spirit of life;<span class="footRef">5</span> and a man who exercises great faith<span class="footRef">6</span> in administering to the
  sick,<span class="footRef">7</span> blessing little children,<span class="footRef">8</span> or confirming,<span class="footRef">9</span> is liable to become weakened.<span class="footRef">10</span> (March 14, 1843.)
  DHC 5:303.</p>
